      &lt;/tr&gt;
  &lt;/thead&gt;
  &lt;tbody&gt;
      &lt;tr&gt;
          &lt;td&gt;Platformer Runner Game&lt;/td&gt;
          &lt;td&gt;C++ + raylib&lt;/td&gt;
          &lt;td&gt;Solo Project&lt;/td&gt;
      &lt;/tr&gt;
  &lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;project-description&#34;&gt;Project Description
&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;This is a solo project I completed during university. The player character runs automatically, dodging enemies and jumping over obstacles to reach the finish line. The gameplay is fast-paced, designed for quick pick-up-and-play sessions and repeated challenges.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;highlights&#34;&gt;Highlights
&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implemented multi-layered background auto-scrolling to enhance visual dynamism&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Developed enemy AI logic including movement, collision detection, and trigger mechanisms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Designed and built a local leaderboard system to track player scores&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Used plain text files for data persistence and retrieval&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;retrospective&#34;&gt;Retrospective
&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;Given the five-week development timeline, I prioritized rapid prototyping to deliver core gameplay features. However, the lack of modular architecture made later feature expansion and maintenance more difficult, highlighting the importance of scalable design.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;next-steps&#34;&gt;Next Steps
&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Introduce object pooling to optimize enemy spawning logic, improving performance and resource management efficiency&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Refactor the project architecture for better modularity and maintainability&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Add a new sliding animation for the player character to enrich movement dynamics&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Implement level data loading from local files to support scalable stage design&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;(Estimated completion: December 2025)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
